"дистрибутиві (Linux) вже встановлено PostgreSQL або ви раніше встановлювали "
"PostgreSQL і забули про це. PostGIS працюватиме лише з PostgreSQL "
"&min_postgres_version; або новішою версією, а використання старішої версії "
"призведе до появи дивних, несподіваних повідомлень про помилки. Щоб "
"перевірити версію PostgreSQL, що працює, під’єднайтеся до бази даних за "
"допомогою psql і виконайте цей запит:"

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are running an RPM based distribution, you can check for the "
"existence of pre-installed packages using the <command>rpm</command> command "
"as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#, no-c-format
msgid "Restoring an upgrade into a database without PostGIS."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your upgrade fails, make sure you are restoring into a database that "
"already has PostGIS installed."
msgstr ""
"Якщо оновлення не вдалося, переконайтеся, що ви відновлюєте дані в базу, в "
"якій вже встановлено PostGIS."

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Also check that configure has correctly detected the location and version of "
"PostgreSQL, the Proj library and the GEOS library."
msgstr ""
"Також перевірте, чи конфігуратор правильно визначив розташування та версію "
"PostgreSQL, бібліотеки Proj та бібліотеки GEOS."

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The output from configure is used to generate the "
"<filename>postgis_config.h</filename> file. Check that the "
"<varname>POSTGIS_PGSQL_VERSION</varname>, <varname>POSTGIS_PROJ_VERSION</"
"varname> and <varname>POSTGIS_GEOS_VERSION</varname> variables have been set "
"correctly."
msgstr ""
"Вихідні дані команди configure використовуються для створення файлу "
"<filename>postgis_config.h</filename>. Перевірте, чи правильно встановлено "
"змінні <varname>POSTGIS_PGSQL_VERSION</varname>, "
"<varname>POSTGIS_PROJ_VERSION</varname> та <varname>POSTGIS_GEOS_VERSION</"
"varname>."

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Вступ"

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "What Is PostGIS?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"PostGIS extends <link xlink:href=\"https://www.postgresql.org/\">PostgreSQL</"
"link> so that geospatial data can be stored, indexed, queried, and processed "
"in the database. It keeps location data beside ordinary relational data, so "
"a spatial query can use the same SQL, transactions, constraints, access "
"controls, backup tools, and application connections as the rest of a "
"PostgreSQL database."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "The main <literal>postgis</literal> extension adds:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<varname>geometry</varname> for planar coordinate systems and "
"<varname>geography</varname> for geodetic coordinates on the earth."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Spatial indexes that let the PostgreSQL planner avoid scanning every row "
"when objects can be filtered by location."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Functions for measurement, relationships, overlays, geometry construction "
"and editing, coordinate transformation, clustering, and spatial data "
"exchange."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Support for common geospatial encodings and formats, including WKT, WKB, "
"GeoJSON, GML, KML, FlatGeobuf, Geobuf, and Mapbox Vector Tiles."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This makes PostgreSQL a spatial database: applications can ask both ordinary "
"questions and location-aware questions without moving data to a separate GIS "
"processing system. Desktop GIS, map servers, ETL tools, and application "
"frameworks can connect through normal PostgreSQL interfaces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "What Is in the PostGIS Distribution?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This manual documents the main PostGIS source distribution. Depending on how "
"PostGIS was built and packaged, it can provide several PostgreSQL extensions "
"and command-line tools:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#, no-c-format
msgid "postgis"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The core geometry and geography types, spatial indexes, and most spatial "
"functions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#, no-c-format
msgid "postgis_raster"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Raster storage, analysis, loading, and export. Raster support uses GDAL and "
"can be omitted from a build."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#, no-c-format
msgid "postgis_topology"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SQL/MM topology types and functions for models based on shared nodes, edges, "
"and faces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#, no-c-format
msgid "postgis_sfcgal"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Additional 2D and 3D processing functions backed by the optional SFCGAL "
"library."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#, no-c-format
